      "writtenOn": "2021-01-15T01:57:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Technically I think the system_shared_libs setting is only needed for libunwind-exported.a, not libunwind.a. I could move the setting to only affect libunwind-exported.a, but then switching libc.so\u0027s dependency from libunwind-exported.a to libunwind.a (e.g. for testing/experimentation) would trigger a mysterious build error, so I think it\u0027s better to clear the setting for both modules. I\u0027ll update the comment.\n\nI wonder if it makes sense that a prebuilt static archive should automatically/implicitly depend on a shared library like libc.so. e.g. Is it useful for the \"system_shared_libs\" property to exist on a Soong module of type \"llvm_prebuilt_library_static\"?",
      "parentUuid": "b0ee8d25_50474487",
      "range": {
