      "writtenOn": "2021-01-15T02:14:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe Soong propagates the dependencies, so that a shared library that links against a prebuilt static library automatically links against the system_shared_libs of the static prebuilt?\n\nlibunwind[-exported].a does actually depend on libc and libdl functions.\n\nThe builtins ought to have the same problem (especially if/when I change libc.so to use a special exported version on arm32/x86), but I see that libClangRtPrebuiltLibraryStatic sets System_shared_libs to [] in clangprebuilts.go. (The builtins call memcpy and abort in libc.)",
